TY  - JOUR
TI  - Existence of a Core When There Are Increasing Returns
AU  - Sharkey, W. W.
AB  - [A model of a cooperative game without side payments is used to study the core of an economy subject to increasing returns. The major result is that quasi-convexity and subhomogeneity of the cost function along with restrictive but plausible conditions on preferences are sufficient for the existence of a core. Implications are considered for both partial and general equilibrium analysis.]
